    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down. | Bromley. | Kent. S.E.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Feb. 16<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>Absence from home during the last ten days must plead my excuse for not having earlier thanked you most sincerely for your kind &amp; to me very valuable letter, which gives me just the facts, which I wanted &amp; which will be very useful to me to quote.<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>with my renewed thanks | Pray believe me | Dear Sir | Yours faithfully &amp; obliged | Charles Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The letter from Briggs has not been found. However, see the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-3963.xml" resp="#automat">letter to J. J. Briggs, 2 February [1863]</ref>, and <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_7951.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Variation</hi></ref> 2: 15–16.</note>
        </div>        
            
